      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Theodore Dreiser (1871-1945) was an American author and journalist who was part of the Naturalist literary movement of the nineteenth century. He is best known for his novels <emph render="italic">Sister Carrie</emph> and <emph render="italic">An American Tragedy</emph>.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Theodore Dreiser Poem </emph>contains an undated, handwritten poem titled "Confeusation" [sic].  The poem is signed by Dreiser and begins, "When I would quarrel with the men of fame / Who proudly ride o'er all. .  ."</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
